What is a complex system?


There are several definitions. Here are some:

‚ÄúSystems that don‚Äôt yield to compact forms of representation or description‚Äù (David Krakauer in Mitchell (2013));
‚ÄúA system of many interacting parts where the system is more than just the sum of its parts‚Äù (Mark Newman in Mitchell (2013));
Systems with many connected agents that interact and exhibit self-organization and emergence behavior, all without the need for a central controller (Camilo Rodrigues Neto).
Dialectics at its finest (my working definition).
